						               													<description>Each player is a traveller with the unique citizenship. For instance, in order to go to the long journey, Russian citizen need to get internation passport. Belarusian citizen has internation passport by default, but he can visit a little amount of countries without visas.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A board is a map of Europe. The goal of the travellers is to collect as many points as they can for visited countries. And this is not always about countries' quantity.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In the beginning of a game a player gets citizenship (Russia, Belarus, Ukraine or Kazakhstan), 100 euro and three bonus cards. A player puts his meeple on the board in a country of his citizenship.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In a player's turn he can do one of the following actions:&amp;#10;- to visit a new country by bus, by plane or &amp;#10;by hitchhiking. A player moves his meeple to new country on the board. In order to do it he needs to pay corresponding money (price for bus travel or plane travel) or roll a dice (using luck in hitchhiking).&amp;#10;- to earn money by working in a player's current country.&amp;#10;- to make Visa (Schengen Visa or UK Visa). Without Visa it is impossible to visit most countries in the game.&amp;#10;- to make international passport.&amp;#10;Also a player in his turn can play bonus cards.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For visiting new country a player gets a flag of the country and gets corresponding points; then he gets a bonus card.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;A game ends when all countries are visited. A player with the most points wins.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
